<h1>Problem 1321 - 2021 IMOSL, N7, CN</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Let \(a_1,a_2,a_3,\ldots\) be an infinite sequence of positive integers such that \(a_{n+2m}\) divides \(a_{n}+a_{n+m}\) for all positive integers \(n\) and \(m.\) Prove that this sequence is eventually periodic, i.e. there exist positive integers \(N\) and \(d\) such that \(a_n=a_{n+d}\) for all \(n>N.\)</p>
